Pre-Game Insights: Georgia and Greece are competing in the UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying round on March 26, 2024.
Georgia finished fourth in Group A and advanced to the playoffs via the Nations League.
Georgia host Greece at the Boris Paichadze Dinamo Arena.
Georgia have a 50% win-draw ratio in their last five games.
Greece won the UEFA European Championship in 2004.
Georgia's key players include Khvicha Kvaratskhelia and Georges Mikautadze.
Greece's key players include Georgios Masouras and Anastasios Bakasetas.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Georgia and Greece have a history of 9 meetings with Greece leading 7 wins and 2 draws.
Others: The match is Georgia's first European Championship final after seven attempts.
Greece are aiming for their fifth participation in the continental competition.
